<TITLE> Weather clears gradually </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 17 (bdnews24.com)The most recent low that brewed in the Bay weakened further Wednesday, but ports continued to hoist local cautionary signal three as the seas were still choppy, weather office said. The southern river ports were advised to keep cautionary signal one until further notice, a bulletin issued Wednesday morning said. Golam Mostafa, duty officer at the Agargaon meteorological directorate, told bdnews24.com at 10:30am that the "well-marked low" weakened and hovered over Dhaka-Comilla region in northeastern Bangladesh. The latest bulletin forecast light to moderate rains accompanied at places with gusty to squally winds and occasional thunderstorm and lightning in Dhaka, Chittagong, Sylhet and Barisal divisions. Rajshahi and Khulna divisions may experience moderate to heavy rainfall at some places, it said. All fishing trawlers and water vessels have been advised to cruise close to the coasts and stay alert. The day temperatures across the country may see a 1-2 degrees Centigrade rise. bdnew
